fluency1: Awkward syntax can go one of two ways - it can feel like a deliberate and strange move that makes the sentence magical (Hemingway was an expert at this) or it can seem simply incorrect. Such was the case with the story I read.
originality1: Working within a particular genre, this writer has to make it feel fresh (the intern facing a difficult choice in a position of powerlessness). Hence, genre writing requires perhaps MORE originality, which is the opposite of what one might think.
elaboration1: Vivid details that flesh a story out (not just a dog, but a dog named Kafka, etc).
